## 1. Executive Summary

The **Plastic Waste Audit & Reduction Tracker** is a full-stack enterprise Java web application built to address the growing global plastic pollution crisis. It enables industries to log, track, and reduce their plastic waste generation while providing government regulators real-time visibility into compliance data.

The system is aligned with **United Nations Sustainable Development Goals** — specifically **SDG 12** (Responsible Consumption & Production) and **SDG 14** (Life Below Water). It calculates key environmental KPIs: Recycling Rate, Reduction Rate, and Ocean-Plastic Prevention metrics.

**Key Highlights:**
- Multi-role web application (Regulator + Industry User views)
- Real-time SDG metric calculation from user-entered data
- AI-powered next-month waste prediction using Linear Regression (no external ML libraries)
- Async multithreaded report generation
- Real-time alert broadcasting via custom Java Socket Server
- Raw JDBC batch import alongside Hibernate/JPA
- Spring Security 6 with role-based access control
- Servlet Filter for full HTTP request audit logging

---

## 2. Project Background & Motivation

Plastic pollution is one of the most critical environmental challenges of the 21st century:

- Over **400 million tons** of plastic are produced globally each year
- Only **9%** of all plastic ever produced has been recycled
- Approximately **8 million tons** of plastic enter the ocean annually
- UN SDG 12 targets responsible production patterns by 2030
- UN SDG 14 aims to prevent marine pollution including plastic waste

**Problem Statement**: Industries lack a standardized, digital system to track plastic waste generation, recycling efforts, and compliance with environmental targets. Government regulators have no unified view of industry-level compliance data.

**Solution**: A centralized digital platform that:
1. Forces industries to log monthly plastic waste data
2. Automatically calculates KPIs aligned to SDG 12 & 14
3. Enables regulators to generate compliance audit reports
4. Uses AI to predict future waste trends and provide actionable recommendations

---

## 3. Objectives & Scope

### Primary Objectives
| # | Objective |
|---|-----------|
| O1 | Enable industry users to log monthly plastic waste data (generated, recycled, eliminated) |
| O2 | Provide role-based dashboards for Regulator (Admin) and Industry views |
| O3 | Calculate SDG 12 & 14 KPIs dynamically from real data |
| O4 | Generate compliance audit reports asynchronously |
| O5 | Predict next-month waste trends using linear regression |
| O6 | Broadcast real-time alerts to connected regulators via Socket |
| O7 | Maintain full HTTP request audit trail via Servlet Filter |
| O8 | Support batch data import via raw JDBC PreparedStatement |

### Scope
- **In Scope**: Industry registration, waste logging, dashboard KPIs, audit reports, AI prediction, socket alerts, batch JDBC
- **Out of Scope**: PDF export (future), mobile app, IoT sensor integration, public API

---

## 4. SDG Alignment & Impact

### SDG 12 — Responsible Consumption & Production

| Target | System Feature |
|--------|---------------|
| 12.4 — Responsible management of chemicals & waste | WasteEntry logging + verified field |
| 12.5 — Substantially reduce waste generation | Annual reduction target per industry |
| 12.6 — Encourage reporting on sustainability | AuditReport generation per industry |

**KPI**: `Reduction Rate = (Recycled + Eliminated) / Generated × 100%`  
**Target**: ≥ 30% reduction rate to classify as COMPLIANT.

### SDG 14 — Life Below Water

| Target | System Feature |
|--------|---------------|
| 14.1 — Prevent marine pollution | `plastic_eliminated_kg` tracks plastic kept out of waterways |
| 14.2 — Protect coastal ecosystems | Recycling Ratio KPI tracks recovery rate |

**KPI**: `Recycling Ratio = Recycled / Generated × 100%`  
**Target**: ≥ 50% recycling ratio (SDG 14 goal).

