## 7. Database Design & ER Diagram

### 7.1 Entity-Relationship Diagram

```mermaid
erDiagram
    ROLES {
        BIGINT id PK
        VARCHAR50 name UK
    }
    USERS {
        BIGINT id PK
        VARCHAR60 username UK
        VARCHAR255 password
        VARCHAR100 email UK
        VARCHAR100 full_name
        TINYINT enabled
        BIGINT industry_id FK
    }
    USER_ROLES {
        BIGINT user_id PK_FK
        BIGINT role_id PK_FK
    }
    INDUSTRIES {
        BIGINT id PK
        VARCHAR150 name
        VARCHAR100 sector
        VARCHAR200 location
        VARCHAR60 registration_no UK
        VARCHAR100 contact_email
        VARCHAR20 contact_phone
        DOUBLE annual_plastic_target_kg
    }
    WASTE_ENTRIES {
        BIGINT id PK
        BIGINT industry_id FK
        DATE entry_date
        DOUBLE plastic_generated_kg
        DOUBLE plastic_recycled_kg
        DOUBLE plastic_eliminated_kg
        VARCHAR30 entry_type
        VARCHAR500 notes
        TINYINT verified
    }
    AUDIT_REPORTS {
        BIGINT id PK
        BIGINT industry_id FK
        BIGINT generated_by_user_id FK
        DATE period_start
        DATE period_end
        DOUBLE total_generated_kg
        DOUBLE total_recycled_kg
        DOUBLE total_eliminated_kg
        DOUBLE reduction_rate_percent
        DOUBLE recycling_ratio_percent
        VARCHAR20 status
        DATETIME generated_at
        VARCHAR1000 remarks
    }

    USERS ||--o{ USER_ROLES : "has"
    ROLES ||--o{ USER_ROLES : "assigned to"
    INDUSTRIES ||--o{ USERS : "employs"
    INDUSTRIES ||--o{ WASTE_ENTRIES : "generates"
    INDUSTRIES ||--o{ AUDIT_REPORTS : "audited by"
    USERS ||--o{ AUDIT_REPORTS : "generated by"
```

### 7.2 Table Descriptions

| Table | Rows (typical) | Description |
|-------|---------------|-------------|
| `roles` | 2 (ADMIN, INDUSTRY) | Static role definitions |
| `users` | N | System users with optional industry link |
| `user_roles` | N×M | Many-to-many join between users and roles |
| `industries` | N | Registered companies with environmental targets |
| `waste_entries` | N×12/year | Monthly plastic waste log per industry |
| `audit_reports` | N | Generated compliance summaries per industry/period |

### 7.3 Key Database Constraints

```sql
-- Referential integrity
FOREIGN KEY (industry_id) REFERENCES industries(id) ON DELETE CASCADE -- waste_entries
FOREIGN KEY (industry_id) REFERENCES industries(id) ON DELETE CASCADE -- audit_reports
FOREIGN KEY (industry_id) REFERENCES industries(id) ON DELETE SET NULL -- users
FOREIGN KEY (generated_by_user_id) REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE SET NULL

-- Business uniqueness
UNIQUE KEY on registration_no (industries)
UNIQUE KEY on username, email (users)
UNIQUE KEY on (user_id, role_id) (user_roles - composite PK)

-- Performance indexes
INDEX idx_we_industry_date ON waste_entries(industry_id, entry_date)
INDEX idx_ar_industry ON audit_reports(industry_id)
INDEX idx_ar_status ON audit_reports(status)
```

