### 9.6 Real-time Alert Socket Module

**Files**: [AlertServer.java](file:///c:/Users/Shuddhodhan/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/PlasticWasteTracker/src/main/java/com/plasticaudit/socket/AlertServer.java), [AlertClient.java](file:///c:/Users/Shuddhodhan/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/PlasticWasteTracker/src/main/java/com/plasticaudit/socket/AlertClient.java)

A custom Java `ServerSocket` (port 9090) running in a daemon thread via `@PostConstruct`. Supports multiple concurrent clients via `CopyOnWriteArrayList<PrintWriter>`.

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant AlertServer
    participant RegulatorClient
    participant BroadcastThread

    AlertServer->>AlertServer: ServerSocket.listen(:9090) [daemon thread]
    RegulatorClient->>AlertServer: TCP connect
    AlertServer->>RegulatorClient: "Connected to PlasticAudit AlertServer"
    RegulatorClient->>AlertServer: "BROADCAST:New waste entry logged"
    AlertServer->>BroadcastThread: broadcastAlert(message)
    loop All connected clients
        BroadcastThread->>RegulatorClient: "[ALERT] New waste entry logged"
    end
```

**Socket Architecture:**

| Component | Detail |
|-----------|--------|
| Server socket | `ServerSocket(9090)` |
| Client handler | One thread per client via `ExecutorService` |
| Message broadcast | `CopyOnWriteArrayList<PrintWriter>` (thread-safe) |
| Timeout | 3 seconds read timeout on [AlertClient](file:///c:/Users/Shuddhodhan/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/PlasticWasteTracker/src/main/java/com/plasticaudit/socket/AlertClient.java#16-56) |
| Shutdown | Daemon thread, closes on JVM exit |

---

### 9.7 JDBC Batch Module

**Files**: [BatchWasteJdbcRepository.java](file:///c:/Users/Shuddhodhan/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/PlasticWasteTracker/src/main/java/com/plasticaudit/jdbc/BatchWasteJdbcRepository.java)

Demonstrates raw JDBC alongside Hibernate. Used for scenarios where Hibernate's overhead is undesirable (e.g., bulk imports of thousands of rows from CSV).

**Features:**
- Manual transaction: `conn.setAutoCommit(false)` / `conn.commit()` / `conn.rollback()`
- Batch flush every 50 rows (configurable)
- `PreparedStatement.addBatch()` / `executeBatch()` for performance
- Fallback summary query via raw `ResultSet`

---

### 9.8 Request Logging Filter

**Files**: [RequestLoggingFilter.java](file:///c:/Users/Shuddhodhan/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/PlasticWasteTracker/src/main/java/com/plasticaudit/filter/RequestLoggingFilter.java)

A standard Servlet [Filter](file:///c:/Users/Shuddhodhan/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/PlasticWasteTracker/src/main/java/com/plasticaudit/filter/RequestLoggingFilter.java#32-64) registered via Spring `@Component`. Logs every HTTP request with:
- Timestamp, HTTP method, URI, query string
- Authenticated username (or ANONYMOUS)
- Client IP, response status code, response time (ms)

Skips static resources (`/css`, `/js`, `/images`) to reduce log noise.

