## 15. Security Architecture

### 15.1 Authentication Flow
- **Mechanism**: Form-based login via Spring Security 6
- **Password Hashing**: BCrypt strength 12
- **Session**: Stateful HTTP session, max 1 concurrent session per user
- **CSRF**: Enabled by default; all POST forms include CSRF token via `th:action`
- **Role detection**: Custom `AuthenticationSuccessHandler` validates submitted role against DB role

### 15.2 Authorization Matrix

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    UA([Unauthenticated]) --> L["/login\n/css/** /js/**"]
    AA([ROLE_ADMIN]) --> L
    AA --> AD["/admin/**\n(users, industries, socket)"]
    AA --> SH["/waste/**\n/reports/**\n/prediction/**\n/dashboard/**"]
    IA([ROLE_INDUSTRY]) --> L
    IA --> SH
```

### 15.3 Data Access Security (Controller Level)
- Industry users can only view/submit their own industry's data
- Cross-industry data access is blocked in [WasteEntryController](file:///c:/Users/Shuddhodhan/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/PlasticWasteTracker/src/main/java/com/plasticaudit/controller/WasteEntryController.java#23-106) and [PredictionController](file:///c:/Users/Shuddhodhan/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/PlasticWasteTracker/src/main/java/com/plasticaudit/prediction/PredictionController.java#21-117)
- Admin bypass enabled by checking `ROLE_ADMIN` authority

