## 16. AI Prediction Algorithm

### 16.1 OLS Simple Linear Regression

The prediction engine implements **Ordinary Least Squares (OLS) regression** — the foundational ML algorithm — in pure Java without any external library.

**Mathematical Model:**

```
y = a + b·x

Where:
  x = month index (0, 1, 2, ..., n-1)
  y = waste metric value (generated / recycled / eliminated)

Slope:      b = (n·Σxy − Σx·Σy) / (n·Σx² − (Σx)²)
Intercept:  a = (Σy − b·Σx) / n

Next month prediction:  y_pred = a + b·n
```

**Java Implementation Snippet:**
```java
private double linearPredict(double[] x, double[] y, int xPredict) {
    int n = x.length;
    double sumX=0, sumY=0, sumXY=0, sumX2=0;
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        sumX  += x[i]; sumY  += y[i];
        sumXY += x[i] * y[i];
        sumX2 += x[i] * x[i];
    }
    double denom = n * sumX2 - sumX * sumX;
    if (denom == 0) return sumY / n;  // flat — return mean
    double b = (n * sumXY - sumX * sumY) / denom;
    double a = (sumY - b * sumX) / n;
    return a + b * xPredict;
}
```

### 16.2 Risk Assessment Logic

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Compute avg recycling rate\ngrowth rate\npredicted reduction] --> B{avgRecycling >= 50%\nAND growth <= 5%\nAND predReduction >= 40%?}
    B -- Yes --> LOW[🟢 LOW Risk]
    B -- No --> C{avgRecycling >= 25%\nOR growth between 5-20%?}
    C -- Yes --> MED[🟡 MEDIUM Risk]
    C -- No --> HIGH[🔴 HIGH Risk]
```

### 16.3 Recommendation Engine

| Condition | Recommendation |
|-----------|---------------|
| `growthRate > 10%` | Audit production processes for single-use plastic substitutes |
| `growthRate > 20%` | Mandatory plastic reduction targets for next quarter |
| `recyclingTrend < -5%` | Increase segregation stations and recycling vendor partners |
| `avgRecyclingRate < 30%` | Invest in material recovery facilities (MRFs) |
| `predictedRecycling < 20%` | Immediate supplier and logistics review recommended |
| `predictedGeneration > 5000 kg` | Evaluate bulk packaging reduction programs |
| `avgReductionRate >= 50%` | Document best practices, replicate across facilities |

### 16.4 Minimum Data Requirement
- **Minimum 3 monthly data points** required for regression
- If < 3: system returns friendly message with entry count and CTA to log more data
- Protects against overfitting on sparse data

