## 22. Conclusion

The **Plastic Waste Audit & Reduction Tracker** successfully demonstrates a complete, full-stack enterprise Java application addressing a real-world environmental challenge. The system covers all layers of modern Java web development:

- **Frontend**: Thymeleaf + Chart.js with role-adaptive views
- **Security**: Spring Security 6 with BCrypt, CSRF protection, role-based access
- **Business Logic**: Multi-threaded async report generation, AI linear regression engine
- **Data Layer**: Dual persistence via Hibernate/JPA + raw JDBC batch operations
- **Infrastructure**: Custom Socket server for real-time alerts, Servlet Filter for audit logging
- **Compliance**: Dynamic calculation of SDG 12 & 14 KPIs

The AI Prediction module uniquely transforms the tracker from a passive data store into an **intelligent decision-support system** — predicting next-month waste trends, assessing compliance risk, and generating actionable recommendations using pure Java OLS regression without reliance on heavyweight ML frameworks.

**The system is production-ready with:**
- ✅ Normalized database schema with FK constraints and performance indexes
- ✅ Role-based access control enforced at both URL and controller level
- ✅ CSRF protection on all state-changing operations
- ✅ Full request audit trail via Servlet Filter
- ✅ Real-time alert broadcasting via custom Socket server
- ✅ Asynchronous report generation without blocking the UI
- ✅ AI-powered prediction with insufficient-data guard and contextual recommendations

